article.headline: New Orleans 74, New Mexico State 71
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Bo McCalebb scored 23 points and New Orleans hit six free throws in the final 15 seconds as the Privateers defeated Sun Belt Conference foe New Mexico State 74-71 Thursday night. Shawn Malloy had his second straight double-double with 11 points 16 rebounds. Chad Barnes added 14 points and Jamie McNeilly scored 11 for New Orleans (7-8, 2-0 Sun Belt). Josh Jenkins led the Aggies (4-11, 0-2) with 23 points and eight assists, while Duane John added 17 points and Mike Mitchell had 10. Barnes drilled a 3-pointer from the corner to give New Orleans a 68-66 lead with 1:24 to go. The Aggies got a layup and a 3-pointer down the stretch to keep the game close, but the Privateers were perfect from the free-throw line over the final minute, hitting six free throws -- four from McCalebb and two from Barnes.
